 The expression $$
\frac{x-3}{2x^2-8x+7}
$$ will be undefined when the denominator is zero. To find the values of $x$ that make the denominator zero, we set the expression equal to zero and solve for $x$. So, we have $$
\frac{x-3}{2x^2-8x+7}
= 0. $$Multiplying by the numerator and denominator gives $$
x-3 = 0. $$This equation放下来可以写为$x=3$. 除了 $x=3$,我们还可以看到分母 $2x^2-8x+7$ 的判别式为 $b^2-4ac = (-8)^2-4(2)(7)=64-56=8$. 判别式的值必须大于零以确保分式有实数解。 因此，当 $x=3$ 时，分母为零，所以这个表达式是未定义的。所以，答案是 $x=3$。
